1. The objective was to describe two acute studies.
2. The studies were randomized.
3. The studies were double-blind.
4. The studies were placebo-controlled.
5. The studies were head-to-head.
6. The studies involved lisdexamfetamine dimesylate (LDX).
7. The studies involved osmotic-release oral system methylphenidate (OROS-MPH).
8. The studies were conducted on adolescents.
9. The adolescents involved in the studies had ADHD.

messages.content:
Statement: Our objective was to describe two acute randomized, double-blind, placebo-controlled, head-to-head studies of lisdexamfetamine dimesylate (LDX) and osmotic-release oral system methylphenidate (OROS-MPH) in adolescents with ADHD.
